<title>PAKISTAN: Pakistani bourse to shut on Friday.</title>
<headline>Pakistani bourse to shut on Friday.</headline>
<dateline>KARACHI, Pakistan 1997-07-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Pakistan's main Karachi Stock Exchange said on Thurday it would remain closed on Friday because of an Islamic religious holiday and would reopen on Monday after the Saturday-Sunday weekend.</p>
<p>On Thursday, the KSE's 100-share index closed 32.52 points, or 1.79 percent, up at 1,845.30 amid 146 losers and 110 gainers. ICI Pakistan closed 1.75 up at 30.40.</p>
<p>($1 = 40.62 rupees)</p>
<p>-- Ibrahim Khan 9221-5685192</p>
